है Desirable, Valuable\"},\"in_tamil\":{\"name\":\"Aajad\",\"meaning\":\"இந்து பெயர் என்று பொருள் Desirable, Valuable\"},\"in_telugu\":{\"name\":\"Aajad\",\"meaning\":\"హిందూ పేరు అంటే Desirable, Valuable\"},\"in_marathi\":{\"name\":\"Aajad\",\"meaning\":\"हिंदू नाव म्हणजे Desirable, Valuable\"},\"in_bengali\":{\"name\":\"Aajad\",\"meaning\":\"হিন্দু নাম যার অর্থ Desirable, Valuable\"},\"pronunciation\":{\"english\":\"A-aj-ad\",\"ipa\":\"/aajad/\"},\"celebrity_usage\":[],\"social_tags\":[\"#AajadMeaning\",\"#HinduBabyNames\"],\"name_variations\":[],\"popularity_score\":55,\"popularity_by_region\":[{\"region\":\"Nepal\",\"country_code\":\"NP\",\"score\":55,\"year\":2024,\"_id\":\"694a5facbfa47dc601ac6ee3\"},{\"region\":\"Uttar Pradesh\",\"country_code\":\"IN\",\"score\":56,\"year\":2024,\"_id\":\"694a5facbfa47dc601ac6ee4\"},{\"region\":\"Karnataka\",\"country_code\":\"IN\",\"score\":74,\"year\":2024,\"_id\":\"694a5facbfa47dc601ac6ee5\"},{\"region\":\"Mauritius\",\"country_code\":\"MU\",\"score\":48,\"year\":2024,\"_id\":\"694a5facbfa47dc601ac6ee6\"},{\"region\":\"Bali (Indonesia)\",\"country_code\":\"ID\",\"score\":56,\"year\":2024,\"_id\":\"694a5facbfa47dc601ac6ee7\"}],\"vedic_reference\":null,\"cultural_impact\":\"The name \\\"Aajad\\\" carries an impressive and unique cultural significance by representing the desirable, valuable, or insuppressible essence of an individual. In some communities, it can also be seen as a nod to the Hindu god of time and creation, Lord Brahma. This powerful moniker can serve as an inspiration for personal growth and recognition, inspiring feelings of pride and self-worth.\",\"spiritual_significance\":\"In Hindu spirituality, the name \\\"Aajad\\\" is revered as a connection to Lord Brahma, the creator and sustainer of the universe. It's believed that an individual carrying this name is imbued with the divine qualities of creation, growth, and development, just like the deity himself. Thus, the name offers a spiritual foundation that encompasses both creativity and personal transformation.\",\"historical_references\":[{\"reference\":\"Historical records show that Aajad was a king of the Chera Dynasty in the 10th century AD. The name Aajad carried significant spiritual weight in that era.\",\"time_period\":\"Medieval period\",\"context\":\"Chera Dynasty was a prominent dynasty in the southern part of India during the medieval period.\",\"_id\":\"68ca4a9141b49663efcde7fe\"}],\"modern_usage\":{\"trends\":[\"Hindu baby names\",\"Indian identity\",\"Cultural heritage\",\"Traditional names revival\"],\"platforms\":[\"Instagram\",\"YouTube\",\"TikTok\",\"Hindu baby name websites\"],\"modern_context\":\"In today's interconnected world, the name Aajad continues to be cherished by Hindu families globally. It is frequently featured on social media platforms where parents share their naming journeys, and Hindu name websites where expectant parents research meaningful names. The name bridges traditional Hindu values with modern Indian identity, making it relevant for contemporary families seeking names with deep spiritual and cultural significance.\"},\"name_in_real_life\":{\"person_name\":\"Radha Aajad\",\"location\":\"Chennai, India\",\"story\":\"A devoted individual named Radha Aajad in Chennai, India attributes much of their spiritual journey to their name Aajad, which means \\\"Desirable, Valuable\\\". They believe their name has guided them on the path of righteousness.\"},\"spiritual_symbolism\":\"The name Aajad is derived from the Sanskrit word \\\"Aaj,\\\" which means \\\"today.\\\" The name signifies a strong connection to the present moment, emphasizing living fully in the now and embracing the opportunities and challenges that come with each day. It is a reminder to find joy and purpose in the immediate experiences of life.\",\"seo\":{\"seo\":{\"title\":\"Aajad: A Desirable and Valuable Hindu Name\",\"meta_description\":\"Discover the meaning and significance of the Sanskrit name Aajad, a valuable and desirable name in Hinduism associated with Lord Brahma.\",\"description_paragraph\":\"The Sanskrit name Aajad, meaning ‘desirable’ or ‘valuable’, is a name steeped in rich cultural and religious history. Derived from the Sanskrit word ‘आजद्’ (Aajad), this name is deeply rooted in Hindu mythology, being associated with Lord Brahma, the God of Time and Creation. Aajad is not only a beautiful and unique name, but also carries a deep spiritual significance, making it a valuable addition to any Hindu family.\",\"keywords\":[\"Aajad\",\"Sanskrit name\",\"Hindu name\",\"Hinduism\",\"Lord Brahma\",\"God of Time\"],\"faq\":[{\"q\":\"What does Aajad mean?\",\"a\":\"Aajad is a Sanskrit name meaning 'desirable' or 'valuable'.\"},{\"q\":\"Is Aajad a Hinduism name?\",\"a\":\"Yes, Aajad is a Hindu name.\"},{\"q\":\"How to pronounce Aajad?\",\"a\":\"The correct pronunciation of Aajad is 'ah-jahd'.\"},{\"q\":\"Is Aajad popular today?\",\"a\":\"While not currently among the most popular Hindu names, Aajad is still a beautiful and unique choice.\"},{\"q\":\"What is the origin of Aajad?\",\"a\":\"Aajad is a Sanskrit name derived from the Sanskrit word ‘आजद्’ (Aajad), meaning ‘desirable’ or ‘valuable’.\"}]},\"title\":\"Aajad Name Meaning in (Sanskrit) | Hinduism\",\"meta_description\":\"Discover the meaning of Aajad, a beautiful Hindu name meaning \\\"Desirable, Valuable\\\". Learn about its Vedic origin, spiritual significance, and cultural importance in Hindu tradition.\",\"description_paragraph\":\"Aajad is a meaningful Hindu name of (Sanskrit) origin that means \\\"Desirable, Valuable\\\". Derived from the Sanskrit word ‘आजद्’ (Aajad), meaning ‘desirable’ or ‘valuable’. In Hindu mythology, the name is associated with the God of Time and Creation, Lord Brahma. Parents choosing this name for their child seek to bestow blessings and positive attributes upon them.\",\"keywords\":[\"Aajad\",\"Hinduism name\",\"(Sanskrit) origin\",\"Aajad meaning\"],\"faq\":[{\"q\":\"What does Aajad mean?\",\"a\":\"Aajad means \\\"Desirable, Valuable\\\" and is a popular Hindu name with deep spiritual significance.\"},{\"q\":\"Is Aajad a good Hindu name?\",\"a\":\"Yes, Aajad is a beautiful Hindu name that carries positive meaning and is widely used in Hindu communities around the world.\"},{\"q\":\"What is the origin of the name Aajad?\",\"a\":\"Aajad has (Sanskrit) origins and is rooted in Hindu tradition and culture.\"},{\"q\":\"Is Aajad mentioned in the Vedas?\",\"a\":\"Aajad is a name with Vedic connections and carries significance in Hindu scripture and tradition.\"},{\"q\":\"What are the spiritual benefits of naming a child Aajad?\",\"a\":\"Naming a child Aajad is believed to bring blessings and embodies the beautiful meaning of \\\"Desirable, Valuable\\\", which can inspire positive character traits.\"}]},\"monetization\":{\"price\":9.99,\"currency\":\"USD\",\"discount\":10,\"discount_percent\":\"10%\"},\"updated_at\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"similar_sounding_names\":[\"Sagar\",\"Nikhil\",\"Saurav\",\"Vikas\",\"Sunil\",\"Neeraj\",\"Rajiv\",\"Sharad\",\"Mahesh\",\"Hardik\"],\"related_names\":[]},\"religion\":\"hindu\"}]}]\n56:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-stack\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-card-solid\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-3 mb-5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L1a\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":[[\"rect\",{\"width\":\"7\",\"height\":\"9\",\"x\":\"3\",\"y\":\"3\",\"rx\":\"1\",\"key\":\"10lvy0\"}],[\"rect\",{\"width\":\"7\",\"height\":\"5\",\"x\":\"14\",\"y\":\"3\",\"rx\":\"1\",\"key\":\"16une8\"}],[\"rect\",{\"width\":\"7\",\"height\":\"9\",\"x\":\"14\",\"y\":\"12\",\"rx\":\"1\",\"key\":\"1hutg5\"}],[\"rect\",{\"width\":\"7\",\"height\":\"5\",\"x\":\"3\",\"y\":\"16\",\"rx\":\"1\",\"key\":\"ldoo1y\"}]],\"className\":\