e.vercel.app\",\"logo\":{\"@type\":\"ImageObject\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/logo.png\",\"width\":512,\"height\":512},\"sameAs\":[\"https://twitter.com/NameVerseOfficial\",\"https://facebook.com/NameVerse\",\"https://instagram.com/nameverse\",\"https://linkedin.com/company/nameverse\"],\"foundingDate\":\"2025\",\"numberOfEmployees\":{\"@type\":\"QuantitativeValue\",\"minValue\":5,\"maxValue\":20},\"contactPoint\":{\"@type\":\"ContactPoint\",\"contactType\":\"customer support\",\"email\":\"hello@nameverse.com\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/contact\"}},\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/hindu/aajad#webpage\"},\"about\":{\"@type\":\"DefinedTerm\",\"@id\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/hindu/aajad#name-term\",\"name\":\"Aajad\",\"description\":\"Desirable\"},\"articleSection\":\"Name Meaning\",\"keywords\":\"Aajad meaning, Aajad origin, Sanskrit linguistics, Hindu names, pronunciation, lucky number, cultural context\",\"wordCount\":500,\"citation\":{\"@type\":\"CreativeWork\",\"name\":\"NameVerse — Cultural Name Knowledge Base\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\"}}6:[\"$\",\"$L2\",null,{\"id\":\"scholarly-article-schema\",\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$e\"}}]\nf:T1ff7,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What does Aajad mean?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The hindu boy name Aajad translates to \\\"Desirable, Valuable\\\" from its Sanskrit roots. This meaning reflects the cultural values embedded in hindu naming traditions.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the origin of the name Aajad?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The name Aajad originates from Sanskrit linguistic tradition and appears across Hindi, Sanskrit, Marathi, Tamil, Telugu, Bengali language communities. NameVerse categorizes it within hindu naming heritage.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Is Aajad a boy, girl, or unisex name?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The name Aajad is listed as Male in hindu naming records. Parents should note that gender classification of names can differ by region and cultural context.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How do you pronounce Aajad?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"To pronounce Aajad correctly, say \\\"A-aj-ad\\\", transcribed as /aajad/ in the International Phonetic Alphabet. The pronunciation balances original Sanskrit phonetics with natural English speech patterns.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the phonetic transcription of Aajad?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Phonetically, Aajad is transcribed as /aajad/. The IPA representation helps linguists and language learners capture the name's authentic Sanskrit pronunciation.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the lucky associations for Aajad?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"For Aajad, Sanskrit naming lore specifies lucky number 5, Friday as the auspicious day, Red, Gold as favourable colors, and Ruby as the protective stone. Such details are traditional rather than scientific.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the numerology of Aajad?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"In numerology, Aajad corresponds to the number 5, with Friday as a significant day, and Ruby as a related gemstone. Numerological analysis assigns meaning based on letter values and phonetic structure.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What personality traits are associated with Aajad?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Within hindu naming traditions, Aajad is linked to personality characteristics such as Brave, Wise, V = Virtuous. These associations influence how the name is perceived in social and cultural contexts.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the cultural significance of Aajad?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Within hindu tradition, Aajad carries cultural weight beyond its literal meaning. Its Sanskrit origins and definition \\\"Desirable, Valuable\\\" position it as a name that connects heritage to contemporary identity. The name \\\"Aajad\\\" carries an impressive and unique cultural significance by representing the desirable, valuable, or insuppressible essence of an individual. In some communities, it can also be seen as a nod to the Hindu god of time and creation, Lord Brahma. This powerful moniker can serve as an inspiration for personal growth and recognition, inspiring feelings of pride and self-worth.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the spiritual meaning of Aajad?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"In spiritual terms, Aajad carries the meaning \\\"Desirable, Valuable\\\". hindu sources elaborate that symbolizes the pursuit of valuable knowledge and wisdom.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What names are similar to Aajad?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Names with similar resonance to Aajad are Sagar, Nikhil, Saurav, Vikas, Sunil, Neeraj. They draw from Sanskrit linguistic sources and maintain thematic connections.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What category does Aajad belong to?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The name Aajad falls under the \\\"Hindu\\\" category within hindu naming classifications. This categorisation helps parents find names that match their thematic preferences.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How is Aajad written in Sanskrit?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"When expressed in Sanskrit, Aajad becomes \\\"हिन्दू नाम जिसका अर्थ है Desirable, Valuable\\\". This translation reflects the name's cross-cultural journey and its integration into sanskrit linguistic norms.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How is Aajad written in Hindi?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Aajad appears in Hindi as \\\"हिन्दू नाम जिसका अर्थ है Desirable, Valuable\\\". This adaptation preserves the name's essential character while conforming to hindi orthographic rules.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the historical background of Aajad?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.999Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The historical background of Aajad reveals: Historical records show that Aajad was a king of the Chera Dynasty in the 10th century AD. The name Aajad carried significant spiritual